# Golden records for go-code retrieval evaluation.
# Lines beginning with '#' and blank lines are skipped.
#
# repo is an absolute local path so the harness hits the already-indexed
# checkout on the krolik box. When running from a different host, override
# with "anatolykoptev/go-code" to force a clone.
#
# LABELING METHOD (documented for honesty / reproducibility)
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Labels were derived by running `mcp__go-code__symbol_search` and
# `mcp__go-code__code_search` against the live MCP and confirming the
# symbol exists in the worktree at HEAD 9c200da (P0-P5 merged).
# Relevance is BINARY: any symbol in expected_top_3 is fully relevant.
# Rigor: heuristic-verified (manually cross-checked via grep / AST search,
# not sampled from production query logs). Known limitation: labels bias
# toward the annotator's mental model of go-code; production distribution
# may differ. A log-sample refresh is recommended before a permanent flip.
#
# ── SECTION 1: Existing seed queries (dense + keyword already covers these) ──
# These queries are included so the A/B harness can confirm sparse does NOT
# REGRESS natural-language descriptive queries (the anti-gaming mix).
#
